In this statement, the President expresses his concern for American citizens who are detained or missing in Iran. He mentions Saeed Abedini, who has been detained for two and a half years, Amir Hekmati, who has been imprisoned for over three and a half years, Jason Rezaian, who has been held for nearly eight months, and Robert Levinson, who has been missing for over eight years. The President calls on the Government of Iran to release these individuals and work with the United States to ensure their safe return to their families. He emphasizes the importance of family and expresses his hope for a joyful spring for everyone.